<p>I’m a multi-disciplinary designer working across all media to understand and implement efficient interactive systems — whether those systems be products, brand identities, books, or spaces. I graduated <em>magna cum laude</em>, with honors, from the Maryland Institute College of Art in 2019 with my BFA in Graphic Design and Critical Theory.</p>
<p>My design practice combines heavy doses of critical and design theory with practical considerations, to interrogate the politics expressed through the acts and artifacts of design.</p>
<p>My rigorous, research-based approach to creative work has led me to develop expertise many areas of design practice, particularly in the disciplines of graphic and product design. Previously, I have been a product designer for Palantir Technologies, Quora, 64 Robots, and Friends of the Web.</p>
